article.headline: Maine 70, New Hampshire 58
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Eric Dobson scored 21 points Wednesday night to lift Maine to an easy 70-58 victory over New Hampshire. Maine jumped out to 31-16 lead with 5:33 to play in the first half and UNH cut that lead to 37-30 at the half, coming within one point, 47-46, in the second half at 12:30. But Maine stretched the lead to 62-51 with 3:52 to play. A Roland Williams three-pointer cut the lead to 10, but UNH never got any closer. For UNH, Ben Sturgill scored 19 points while Craig Walls added 12. Kevin Reed and Mark Flavin each added 10 points for Maine. Dobson also had six assists, two steals and a blocked shot. Maine is 9-5 overall and 3-2 in America East, UNH 4-11 and 0-5.
